---
import Wave from "./Wave.astro"
---

<section class="hidden md:flex w-full h-full justify-center items-center overflow-hidden absolute">
    <p class="absolute left-5  text-pink-500/20 text-9xl font-bold"  style="writing-mode: vertical-rl; text-orientation: mixed;">Projects</p>
        <div class="w-[60%] h-[40rem] gap-10 flex center font-semibold border-4 overflow-hidden rounded-4xl p-8 bg-pink-100 relative">
        <Wave />
        <div class="w-1/2 z-10">
            <div class="flex flex-col justify-between h-full w-full gap-10">
                <div class="w-full ">
                    <img src="/images/project1.webp" class="w-full rounded-2xl border-4 shadow-pink-400/20 shadow-lg" alt="">
                </div>

                <div class="flex flex-col gap-5">
                        <div class="flex gap-5">
                            <h3 class="text-2xl font-medium  text-pink-100"><span class="text-3xl font-bold">Project Name:</span> Linux Dotfiles</h3>
                        </div>
                        <div class="">
                            <h3 class="text-3xl text-pink-100 "><span class="text-3xl font-bold">Difficulty:</span> &#9733; &#9733; &#9733; &#9734; &#9734; </h3>
                        </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="w-1/2 flex flex-col gap-5 z-10">
            <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-pink-500">Project Description</h3>
            <div class="p-2 border-2 rounded-2xl bg-white/10 backdrop-blur-9xl shadow-lg">
                <p class="text-xl font-medium">Linux dotfiles are hidden configuration files (starting with a .) located in a user's home directory. These files control the behavior, appearance, and functionality of various applications, tools, and the overall system. Common examples include .bashrc, .vimrc, .config/, and .Xresources. By customizing dotfiles, users can personalize their Linux environment to enhance aesthetics, improve productivity, and create a unique computing experience.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="absolute bottom-8 right-8">
            <button class="bg-pink-500 hover:bg-pink-400 text-white font-bold py-2 px-4 rounded-full border-3 border-black transition ease-in-out duration-200">
                See Project
            </button>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>